# Trello credentials for the kanban workflow.
# See .claude/skills/kanban/SETUP.md for the full walkthrough.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the three values. .env.local is
# gitignored — never commit it.
#
# 1. API key: visit https://trello.com/power-ups/admin, create a Power-Up
#    named "projitect-kanban" (workspace = whichever workspace owns your
#    board), open it, go to the "API Key" tab, click "Generate a new API
#    Key". Paste here.
#
# 2. Token: visit
#    https://trello.com/1/authorize?expiration=never&scope=read,write&response_type=token&name=projitect-kanban&key=YOUR_API_KEY
#    (substitute YOUR_API_KEY into the URL). Click Allow. Paste the
#    returned token here.
#
# 3. Board ID: open your Trello board in a browser. The URL looks like
#    https://trello.com/b/abc12345/projitect — the segment after /b/ is
#    the short ID. /kanban-init resolves it to the full 24-char ID.
#
#    **Optional on first run.** Leave TRELLO_BOARD_ID blank and /kanban-init
#    will create the board for you interactively (asks for workspace, name,
#    visibility), then tell you the new ID to paste back here. Either way,
#    /kanban-init populates .claude/kanban.json with the per-list IDs.

TRELLO_API_KEY=
TRELLO_TOKEN=
TRELLO_BOARD_ID=
